Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State, has dissolved his cabinet.
The governor, who took the action Wednesday shortly after the validetory session of the state Executive Council meeting at the Government House, told the dissolved appointees to hand over to their permanent secretaries and most senior officers in the state MDAs.
Categories of those affected include, commissioners, Special Advisers and the Secretary to the State Government.
Meanwhile the governor excluded his Chief Press Secretary, Accountant General and Auditor General from the dissolution.
He thanked the former officials for their contributions to the state.